io.neba.api.resourcemodels

Interface AnnotatedFieldMapper.OngoingMapping<FieldType,AnnotationType>

  • Enclosing interface:
    AnnotatedFieldMapper<FieldType,AnnotationType extends Annotation>

    public static interface AnnotatedFieldMapper.OngoingMapping<FieldType,AnnotationType>
    Represents the contextual data of a field mapping during a resource to model mapping.
    Author:
    Olaf Otto

    • Method Detail

      • getResolvedValue

        FieldType getResolvedValue()
        Returns:
        The currently resolved value of the field, or null if no value could be resolved for the field. This value has not been set to the field at this point.

      • getAnnotation

        AnnotationType getAnnotation()
        Returns:
        The instance of the annotation this mapper is registered for. Never null.

      • getModel

        Object getModel()
        Returns:
        The mapped model. At this point, the mapping is still incomplete and no post-processors have been invoked on the model. Never null.

      • getField

        Field getField()
        Returns:
        the mapped field. Never null. The field's value was not changed at this point, i.e. it is likely to deviate from getResolvedValue(). Note: do not rely on this field's type but use the provided field type instead, as these types may be different, for instance in case of Optional fields.

      • getAnnotationsOfField

        Map<Class<? extends Annotation>,Annotation> getAnnotationsOfField()
        Returns:
        All annotations (including meta-annotations, i.e. annotations of annotations) present on the field. Never null.

      • getFieldType

        Class<?> getFieldType()
        Returns:
        The mapped type of the field. Note: In case the field is Optional, this type is the component type, i.e. the type targeted by the optional field. However, field mappers are not applied optional fields but to the subsequent mapping, when the {@link Optional#get() optional value is actually mapped. Never null.

      • getFieldTypeParameter

        Class<?> getFieldTypeParameter()
        Returns:
        the generic type parameter of the field type, or null if no such parameter exists.

      • getRepositoryPath

        String getRepositoryPath()
        Returns:
        the repository path that shall be resolved to the field's value, as determined by the field name or path annotation. Placeholders in the path are resolved at this point. Never null.

      • getResource

        org.apache.sling.api.resource.Resource getResource()
        Returns:
        The resource that is mapped to the model. Never null, but may be a synthetic resource.

      • getProperties

        org.apache.sling.api.resource.ValueMap getProperties()
        Returns:
        The ValueMap representation of the resource. This value map does support primitive types, e.g. int.class. May be null if the resource has no properties, e.g. if it is synthetic.
